        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2464826250" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7233670199199419057">It&apos;s the simple things in life that keep us from going crazy.&apos;<br/>A small room is among the simplest of things, but it is the perception of the person, living in it, that makes it extraordinary. Such is the small room where Ruskin Bond lives. But this small room has provided the world with the greatest of stories. It needs the inspiration to create something. Mr Bond&apos;s inspiration came through this room. Standing beside the window of the room, Mr Bond&apos;s imagination took flight, inspired by the reali</span>
  <span id="freeText7233670199199419057" style="display:none">It's the simple things in life that keep us from going crazy.'<br />A small room is among the simplest of things, but it is the perception of the person, living in it, that makes it extraordinary. Such is the small room where Ruskin Bond lives. But this small room has provided the world with the greatest of stories. It needs the inspiration to create something. Mr Bond's inspiration came through this room. Standing beside the window of the room, Mr Bond's imagination took flight, inspired by the reality of the world seen through the window. This window to the world brought showers of rain, the smell of the earth after rain, the soothing warmth of winter sunlight, and the magic of early dawn of the hills. It is with this sense of awe that Mr Bond penned down the life of the hills and around.<br />There's everything in this book- tales of trees, chirping of birds, sounds of insects, the wetness of the rain, cooling breeze on your warm cheeks, love and loss of some dear ones, and the love for simplest of things. You'll be tempted to open that part of your cupboard where you have kept some things as memories of the bygone days. It will take you to your window or terrace in the early hours of dawn. This book is a comfort book. It takes you on a tour of simple things around you that you sometimes fail to notice in the humdrum of life in the crowded world. It lets your mind calm and shuts down every noise around you so that you can experience the bliss of silence.<br />It is for the second time that I have read this book. It is among my most loved books by Ruskin sir. There are some books that you will never give to someone else because these have become personal to such an extent that you don't want to share the joy of just looking at them with anyone else. This is one such book for me.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7233670199199419057" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


