  <span id="freeText12051677432940856149" style="display:none">It was my second of the Ruskin Bond novellas and it was really nice. Have liked the first half of the book very much where the writer has put in deep messages with brilliant endings to the stories. Masterclass from Bond. <br />In the second half of the book, he has taken me through the nature. As if I have toured the hills, roads of plains including but not limited to Delhi and my very own Meerut. I have never noticed the nature the way it is described in here. And of course, the love of the book that Mr. Bond has been able to describe is also worth mentioning. <br />Overall, 3/5. Little low on rating for far more akin stories are there during the second half of the book. Would have loved a little more variety during the fag-end of the book. <br />In the end...have loved the cover page of the book. Have never seen a cover page as awesome as this one before.</span>
