<div id="review_761286035" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/761286035" />
    <a title="Suzanne" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/21323316-suzanne"><img alt="Suzanne" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1408097105p2/21323316.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/761286035?book_show_action=true">Nov 10, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Suzanne" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Suzanne" href="/user/show/21323316-suzanne">Suzanne</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/21323316-suzanne?shelf=india">india</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer761286035" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1949918810942794083">In his 75th year Ruskin Bond looks back on his life with brief reflections on what was important to him, some of which have been published previously. These are intimate notes, but strangely devoid of people except for his father, lost when he was very young, but who still retains a deep hold on his devoted son. Then there is the old peanut seller, not alone but surely lonely. For the most part, Ruskin reflects on the pleasure that nature brings him. These are peaceful reflections which also ena</span>
  <span id="freeText1949918810942794083" style="display:none">In his 75th year Ruskin Bond looks back on his life with brief reflections on what was important to him, some of which have been published previously. These are intimate notes, but strangely devoid of people except for his father, lost when he was very young, but who still retains a deep hold on his devoted son. Then there is the old peanut seller, not alone but surely lonely. For the most part, Ruskin reflects on the pleasure that nature brings him. These are peaceful reflections which also enable the reader to step back and consider what really matters to them. Another element is the quiet satisfaction that emerges from having lived a life doing what he wanted to do - putting words together and telling stories. Perhaps this can encourage others to take similar steps.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1949918810942794083" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


